musical /ˈmjuːzɪkəl/

(musicals) 

1. ADJ You use musical to indicate that something is connected with playing or studying music. 关于音乐的 [ADJ n] 

例： We have a wealth of musical talent in this region. 我们在该地区有丰富的音乐人才。 

2. musically ADV 关于音乐地 

例： Musically there is a lot to enjoy. 在音乐方面有许多可欣赏。 

3. N-COUNT A musical is a play or film that uses singing and dancing in the story. 音乐剧; 音乐歌舞片 

例： ...the smash hit musical, Miss Saigon. …轰动一时的音乐剧《西贡小姐》。 

4. ADJ Someone who is musical has a natural ability and interest in music. 有音乐天赋的; 喜爱音乐的 

例： I came from a musical family. 我来自一个音乐家庭。 

5. ADJ Sounds that are musical are light and pleasant to hear. 悦耳的 

例： He had a soft, almost musical voice. 他有着轻柔悦耳的嗓音。

